      "heading": "operator module approach",
      "body": "import operator\n\ndef factorial(n):\n    if operator.eq(n, 0) or operator.eq(n, 1):\n        return 1\n    else:\n        return operator.mul(n, factorial(operator.sub(n, 1)))\n\ndef main():\n    try:\n        number = int(input('Enter a number: '))\n        if operator.lt(number, 0):\n            print('Factorial is not defined for negative numbers.')\n        else:\n            print(f'The factorial of {number} is {factorial(number)}')\n    except ValueError:\n        print('Please enter a valid integer.')\nmain()"
